radiographic_examinations.findings: The appendix is visualized in the right pelvis and appears prominent in size, measuring approximately 8 mm. There is air seen within the tip of the appendix; the tip appears slightly thickened and hyperenhancing. No mesenteric stranding is present. The lung bases are clear, and the visualized heart and pericardium are unremarkable. The liver enhances homogenously without any focal lesions. The kidneys enhance and excrete contrast symmetrically without any focal lesions or hydronephrosis. No free fluid, free air, or lymphadenopathy is seen in the abdomen or pelvis.
